Taita Taveta county nominates its ODM candidates for the August 8 elections today.The main battle is expected in the race for governor, where incumbent John Mruttu will square it out with National Assembly minority whip Thomas Mwadeghu. Richard Tairo will face off with Jones Mwaruma for the senator ticket.The aspirants have been holding road shows in a bid to convince voters to support them.Yesterday, Mruttu expressed fears the party was ill-prepared for the Taita Taveta county nominations.The main battle is expected in the race for governor, where incumbent John Mruttu will square it out with National Assembly minority whip Thomas Mwadeghu. Speaking at a local radio station, Mruttu alleged five panelists had recently met at Mwadeghus&rsquo; home.